===Etymology===
From the [[w:Ancient Rome|Ancient Roman]] practice of paying [[soldier#Noun|soldiers]] a {{m|la|salārium}} or [[wage#Noun|wage]] with which to buy [[salt#Noun|salt]].<ref>{{R:Phrase Finder|entry=Worth one’s salt|url=https://www.phrases.org.uk/meanings/worth-ones-salt.html|nodot=1}}; {{cite-web|title=Worth one’s salt|url=http://www.word-detective.com/2007/07/worth-ones-salt/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806044007/http://www.word-detective.com/2007/07/worth-ones-salt/|archivedate=6 August 2019|work=The Word Detective|date=31 July 2007}}.</ref>

